commentTextItems.html: down legside flicked in the air and lands over the boundary at long leg and followed by a stupid field invasion

commentPostTextItems.html: Pakistan win by virtue of an England concession
a massive pitch invasion as azhar flicks one down to long leg for 4 or 6 not sure what was called Pakistan still need runs to win this game
one of the stewards has been injured in the celebratory invasion
word is the england team have conceded to avoid a return to the field

commentTextItems.html: worked off his legs down behind square leg and Azhar just gets back in time

dismissalText.commentary: Abdul Razzaq c †Stewart b Cork 75 (103b 7x4 1x6 141m) SR: 72.81

commentTextItems.html: down the track moving to leg cross bats, seems to take the toe of the bat through to the keeper

commentPostTextItems.html: Azhar has tucked one behind square leg and been slow to turn for the second we have a tv replay decision on a run out at the strikers end
very close hard to tell from the first replay

milestones.description: Darren Gough and Ben Hollioake's 67-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 62 between Dermot Reeve and Darren Gough
Darren Gough has become the top wicket-taker for ENG in ODIs with 147 wickets, going past Ian Botham's 145

stories.title: A day of shame for cricket
stories.summary: It was only a few days ago that a headline like that was confined to events of a purely cricketing nature, such as when England reached an all-time low by being bowled out for just 84 by Australia at Old Trafford to lose a match in the NatWest Series

stories.title: Stewart concedes defeat after another pitch invasion
stories.summary:
A pitch invasion in which a ground steward was injured marred the end of
England's NatWest Series match against Pakistan at Headingley

stories.title: Hollioake lifts England after devastating spell by Waqar
stories.summary:
A dashing half-century from Ben Hollioake restored some of England's
battered pride at Headingley after a sensational spell of fast bowling by
Waqar Younis had reduced the home side to 58 for 7
